{
  "texts": [
    "The widespread application of large language models (LLMs) has progressed at an unprecedented pace and scale in our daily lives [111].",
    "Such a widespread application exposes several vulnerabilities inherent to LLMs, such as data poisoning [55,37], prompt injections [76,101], and hallucinations [53,136,86,12].",
    "For example, prompt injections can exploit a model's propensity to disclose information, resulting in significant data leakage, like leaking personally identifiable information (PII) to an unauthorized user [123,20].",
    "Although numerous studies have attempted to address these issues [129,2], there remains no effective mitigation strategies capable of addressing growing concerns about these issues in LLMs [123,40,71].",
    "Typically, defensive strategies against these threats are implemented through established * These authors contributed equally to this work."
  ]
}